	<h2><img height="189" align="left" width="200" class="thumbnailimg" alt="Sample Image" src="http://graphics.ics.uci.edu/drupal/img/2007a.jpg" /></h2>
<h2>Perception Based Image Processing</h2>
<p align="justify"><span class="left"><b>Overview:</b> Study of contrast sensitivity of the human eye shows that our suprathreshold contrast sensitivity follows the Weber Law and, hence, increases proportionally with the increase in the mean local luminance. In this project, we effectively apply this fact to design a contrast-enhancement method for images that improves the local image contrast by controlling the local image gradient with a single parameter. </span><em><strong> </strong></em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Publications:</p>
